SIMPLE: toe
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toe
<hw>Toe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>too</ets>,
<ets>taa</ets>, AS. <ets>t⟦amac⟧</ets>; akin to D. <ets>teen</ets>, G.
<ets>zehe</ets>, OHG. <ets>z⟦emac⟧ha</ets>, Icel. <ets>t⟦amac⟧</ets>,
Sw. <ets>t⟦aring⟧</ets>, Dan. <ets>taa</ets>; of uncertain origin.
⟦root⟧60.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the terminal
members, or digits, of the foot of a man or an animal.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Each
one, tripping on his <xex>toe</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The fore part of the hoof or foot
of an animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything, or any part, corresponding to the toe of
the foot; <as>as, the <ex>toe</ex> of a boot; the <ex>toe</ex> of a
skate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The journal, or
pivot, at the lower end of a revolving shaft or spindle, which rests in
a step.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A lateral projection at one end, or
between the ends, of a piece, as a rod or bolt, by means of which it is
moved.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A projection from the periphery of a
revolving piece, acting as a cam to lift another piece.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Toe biter</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a tadpole; a
polliwig.</cd> -- <col><b>Toe drop</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
morbid condition of the foot in which the toe is depressed and the heel
elevated, as in <xex>talipes equinus</xex>. See
<er>Talipes</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Toe
<hw>Toe</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Toed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Toeing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To touch or reach with the toes;
to come fully up to; <as>as, to <ex>toe</ex> the mark</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Toe
<hw>Toe</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To hold or carry the toes (in a
certain way).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To toe in</b></col>, <cd>to stand or carry the feet in
such a way that the toes of either foot incline toward the other.</cd>
-- <col><b>To toe out</b></col>, <cd>to have the toes of each foot, in
standing or walking, incline from the other foot.</cd></cs> <--
(Automobiles) <col><b>toe in</b></col>, to align the front wheels so
that they point slightly toward each other. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toed</ent>⟦br⟧
